driven by : ~에 이쓸린
impression : an idea or opinion of what something or someone is like
interpret : to decide what the intended meaning of something is:
encounter : to meet someone unexpectedly:
unless : except if:
perception : a belief or opinion, often held by many people and based on how things seem:
fairly(adverb) : more than average, but less than very:
adjust(v) : to change something slightly, especially to make it more correct, effective, or suitable:
bias/ˈbaɪ.əs/(n) : the action of supporting or opposing a particular person or thing in an unfair way, 
                   because of allowing personal opinions to influence your judgment:  복수:biases
exclusion(n)( C or U ) : the act of not allowing someone or something to take part in an activity or to enter a place:
whether : (used especially in reporting questions and expressing doubts) if, or not:
therefore(adv) : for that reason:
conversely(adv) : in an opposite way:
burdensome/ˈbɜː.dən.səm/(adj) : causing difficulties or work:

in order to : (목적)위하여
the case : 사실
be around : 1(잠자리에서) 일어나다, 찾아오다 2.부근에 있다, 체재하다 3.활동하고 있다
associate with : ~와 어올리다.
as a result : ~결과로서
on the other hand : 다른 한편으로는, 반면에
it is for this reason that: 이 때문에

